From 9d55fb4ce46cd8e7c43374aeb10823d16893e17e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aaradhana Sahu <aaradhana.sahu@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 16 Jul 2025 14:42:47 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: CP: PLATFORM: wifi: ath12k: Add support for
 powering down Q6

In the current MLO (multi-link operation) implementation, the driver
may activate and operate only a single band, but all Q6 to remain
powered on, leading to unnecessary power consumption.

To optimize power usage, this change introduces support for powering
down the Q6 associated with inactive bands.

Note: In MLO mode, the firmware expects either all Q6 to be powered on
or only one, depending on the active band configuration.

Patch-dependency: "UPSTREAM:CP:wifi:ath12k: ErP support"
Patch-work: none

Signed-off-by: Aaradhana Sahu <aaradhana.sahu@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
